, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Bonbury","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Banbury, a place in Oxfordshire, named with the unattested Old English personal name <i>Ban(n)a</i> + Old English <i>burh</i> ‘fort’ (dative <i>byrig</i>). It may also be from the much smaller Banbury in Broadwoodwidger (Devon)."],"variants":[{"name":"Bembry","meanings":["Perhaps an altered form of English   Banbury  ."]}]},{"name":"Agnes","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Latinized version of the Greek name <i>Hagnē</i>, from the feminine form of the adjective <i>hagnos</i> ‘pure, holy’. This was the name of a young Roman virgin martyred in the persecutions instigated by the Roman emperor Diocletian in   ad  303 . She became a very popular saint in the Middle Ages. Her name was early associated with Latin <i>agnus</i> ‘lamb’, leading to the consistent dropping of the initial <i>H-</i> and to her representation in art accompanied by a lamb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes de Bonbury was born about 1259, in Beeston, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. She married Lord David de Beeston in 1289, in Beeston, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died after 1340, in her hometown."},"et":{"Abt 1259–Aft 1340":"umbes 1259–pärast 1340","1245–1312":"1245–1312","1290–1342":"1290–1342","1259–1340":"1259–1340","1259":"1259","1312":"1312","1289":"1289","1245":"1245","1342":"1342","Abt 1259":"umbes 1259","1340":"1340","Aft 1340":"pärast 1340","1290":"1290","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Beeston, Cheshire, England":"Beeston, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1259–Aft 1340":"noin 1259–1340 jälkeen","1245–1312":"1245–1312","1290–1342":"1290–1342","1259–1340":"1259–1340","1259":"1259","1312":"1312","1289":"1289","1245":"1245","1342":"1342","Abt 1259":"noin 1259","1340":"1340","Aft 1340":"1340 jälkeen","1290":"1290","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Beeston, Cheshire, England":"Beeston, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1259–Aft 1340":"environ 1259–après 1340","1245–1312":"1245–1312","1290–1342":"1290–1342","1259–1340":"1259–1340","1259":"1259","1312":"1312","1289":"1289","1245":"1245","1342":"1342","Abt 1259":"environ 1259","1340":"1340","Aft 1340":"après 1340","1290":"1290","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Beeston, Cheshire, England":"Beeston, Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Agnes de Bonbury est née environ 1259, à Beeston, Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a épousé Lord David de Beeston en 1289, à Beeston, Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Elle est décédée après 1340, dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"Abt 1259–Aft 1340":"um 1259–nach 1340","1245–1312":"1245–1312","1290–1342":"1290–1342","1259–1340":"1259–1340","1259":"1259","1312":"1312","1289":"1289","1245":"1245","1342":"1342","Abt 1259":"um 1259","1340":"1340","Aft 1340":"nach 1340","1290":"1290","Cheshire, England":"Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","Beeston, Cheshire, England":"Beeston, Cheshire, Engl